WEBVTT

00:01.333 --> 00:03.635
I'm telling you, Emma.
A little sun,

00:03.669 --> 00:06.337
a little surf,
a little cold one--

00:06.372 --> 00:08.439
life does not get
any better than this.

00:09.608 --> 00:12.310
Hello? Sorry I'm late.
My flip-flops

00:12.344 --> 00:13.611
flopped out
around 14th.

00:15.347 --> 00:17.281
- What's going on?
- Welcome to Wheeler beach,

00:17.447 --> 00:19.781
where strangers don't ask you
to rub lotion on their back.

00:20.747 --> 00:24.050
Snow cones? One of the benefits
of never de-frosting the freezer.

00:24.052 --> 00:25.786
Listen...

00:25.821 --> 00:27.788
Your current
flavor choices include

00:27.823 --> 00:28.956
beer

00:28.990 --> 00:29.990
or ketchup.

00:31.727 --> 00:33.728
I recommend the combo.

00:33.762 --> 00:36.664
Oh, I thought we were going
to the real beach.

00:36.698 --> 00:39.667
You know, where I get to ask
strangers to rub lotion on my back.

00:39.701 --> 00:42.002
We were. Unfortunately,
I got called into work.

00:42.037 --> 00:43.671
But it's the hottest day
of the year.

00:43.705 --> 00:46.607
What kind of crazy person
is even gonna be out?

00:46.641 --> 00:48.709
Merry Christmas,
everybody!

00:48.744 --> 00:50.878
Are you all ready
to revive

00:50.912 --> 00:53.013
a cherished Wheeler
family tradition?

00:53.048 --> 00:55.783
All right!
Pancake-eating contest!

00:56.985 --> 01:00.588
No. The annual
Christmas card photo.

01:00.622 --> 01:01.756
It was Benji's idea.

01:01.790 --> 01:03.724
Whoo!
Family photo!

01:05.861 --> 01:08.529
There really is just no way
to make that sound exciting.

01:08.563 --> 01:11.532
Yeah. Because Mom used
to dress us up like reindeer

01:11.566 --> 01:13.667
and make us look
like idiots.

01:13.702 --> 01:14.835
I know. But now
that Emma's here,

01:14.870 --> 01:15.936
I wanna dress her up
like a reindeer

01:15.971 --> 01:17.571
and make <i>her</i> look
like an idiot.

01:18.707 --> 01:20.608
Aww, I always loved
that card.

01:20.642 --> 01:21.909
It was the highlight
of the season.

01:21.943 --> 01:22.977
Thank you, Riley.

01:23.011 --> 01:26.013
We put it on our fridge,
and laughed...

01:27.949 --> 01:31.786
In admiration
whenever we saw it.

01:31.820 --> 01:34.622
Well, I'm glad you liked it
because you're gonna be in it.

01:34.656 --> 01:36.023
You too, Tuck.
This is about family

01:36.057 --> 01:37.758
and you're both part
of Emma's family now.

01:37.793 --> 01:39.026
Well, God knows
she needs a new one

01:39.060 --> 01:40.928
since your father
blew up the old one.

01:41.462 --> 01:43.898
Ooh, beer cone! Mm.

01:45.834 --> 01:47.802
I actually just finished
cutting his fat head out

01:47.836 --> 01:48.969
of all of our albums.

01:49.504 --> 01:51.839
But you guys got divorced
over three years ago.

01:51.873 --> 01:53.774
Yeah, well, I spent the first two
years trying to ruin his credit.

01:53.809 --> 01:55.042
And then I just
kind of landed on this.

01:56.845 --> 01:57.878
Hey, Tuck.

01:57.913 --> 01:59.647
As the newest member
of the Wheeler clan,

01:59.681 --> 02:01.682
any way I can talk you
into taking my mom's car

02:01.716 --> 02:03.584
out to Jersey tomorrow
to pick up the costumes?

02:03.618 --> 02:05.753
Oh, you know
I don't really drive.

02:05.787 --> 02:07.822
Oh, I do! I'll drive.
Can I do it?

02:07.856 --> 02:09.622
I'm a new member too.

02:10.792 --> 02:12.560
Well, why can't I go?
What's going on?

02:12.594 --> 02:14.562
Well, you know how
it wouldn't be Christmas

02:14.596 --> 02:16.730
- without Santa?
- But Dad was always Santa!

02:18.834 --> 02:21.702
And his sleigh lands
tomorrow morning.

02:21.736 --> 02:23.971
Your father
is coming to town?!

02:24.005 --> 02:25.773
Merry Christmas!

02:28.910 --> 02:31.879
<i>♪ It's amazing
how the unexpected ♪</i>

02:31.913 --> 02:34.982
<i>♪ can take your life
and change direction. ♪</i>

02:34.983 --> 02:38.953
<font color="#ff8c00">Sync & corrections by Alice</font>
<font color="#ff8c00">www.addic7ed.com</font>

02:38.954 --> 02:40.754
Okay, Mom, Dad will
be here any minute.

02:40.789 --> 02:42.756
And I'm begging you--
one weekend,

02:42.791 --> 02:44.758
one photo,
no fighting.

02:44.793 --> 02:46.894
Hey, I'm not the one
you need to worry about.

02:46.928 --> 02:48.896
I have moved on.

02:48.930 --> 02:51.732
Ray Wheeler is just
a speed bump in

02:51.766 --> 02:53.634
my rearview mirror.

02:53.668 --> 02:54.969
I wouldn't mind slamming
the car in reverse

02:55.003 --> 02:55.970
- and backing up--
- Mom!

02:56.004 --> 02:57.972
All right.

02:58.006 --> 02:59.874
Danny, back me up here.

02:59.908 --> 03:02.610
Dude, there are some things in life
you just don't get in between.

03:02.644 --> 03:04.778
a bear and its cub,
a zombie and a brain,

03:04.813 --> 03:05.913
and Mom and Dad fighting.

03:07.682 --> 03:08.816
<i>That's him!</i>

03:08.850 --> 03:09.817
Mom, remember--

03:09.851 --> 03:10.818
How he crushed my soul

03:10.852 --> 03:11.919
and left my ego for dead?

03:11.953 --> 03:14.555
Distant memory. Okay?

03:15.557 --> 03:16.957
- Dad!
- Ben Ben!

03:16.992 --> 03:18.659
Oh!

03:18.693 --> 03:19.960
Oh, you're looking good
as always.

03:19.995 --> 03:22.630
- Hey, Dad!
- Dan the man!

03:22.664 --> 03:23.964
- Think fast!
- Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh.

03:26.868 --> 03:28.903
There she is.

03:28.937 --> 03:31.705
Oh!

03:31.740 --> 03:34.675
Hi. Hi.

03:34.709 --> 03:36.911
I think we know where she gets
her good looks from, huh?

03:40.649 --> 03:43.584
There's a sound I haven't
missed once.

03:43.618 --> 03:45.052
Grab the baby.

03:47.022 --> 03:48.689
Bonnie.

03:49.691 --> 03:50.858
Ray.

03:52.000 --> 03:58.074
